## System Precompile Interface (Address: `0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000900`)

### Complete Solidity Interface

```solidity
// SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT
pragma solidity ^0.8.0;

address constant SYSTEM_ADDR = 0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000900;

interface ISystem {
    function hashBlake256(bytes memory input) external pure returns (bytes32 digest);
    function hashBlake128(bytes memory input) external pure returns (bytes32 digest);
    function toAccountId(address input) external view returns (bytes memory account_id);
    function callerIsOrigin() external view returns (bool);
    function callerIsRoot() external view returns (bool);
    function minimumBalance() external view returns (uint);
    function ownCodeHash() external view returns (bytes32);
    function weightLeft() external view returns (uint64 refTime, uint64 proofSize);
    function terminate(address beneficiary) external;
    function sr25519Verify(uint8[64] calldata signature, bytes calldata message, bytes32 publicKey) external view returns (bool);
    function ecdsaToEthAddress(uint8[33] calldata publicKey) external view returns (bytes20);
}
```

---

### All Function Signatures

| Function | Mutability | Returns |
|----------|-----------|---------|
| `hashBlake256(bytes memory input)` | `pure` | `bytes32 digest` |
| `hashBlake128(bytes memory input)` | `pure` | `bytes32 digest` |
| `toAccountId(address input)` | `view` | `bytes memory account_id` |
| `callerIsOrigin()` | `view` | `bool` |
| `callerIsRoot()` | `view` | `bool` |
| `minimumBalance()` | `view` | `uint` |
| `ownCodeHash()` | `view` | `bytes32` |
| `weightLeft()` | `view` | `uint64 refTime, uint64 proofSize` |
| `terminate(address beneficiary)` | non-payable | — |
| `sr25519Verify(uint8[64], bytes, bytes32)` | `view` | `bool` |
| `ecdsaToEthAddress(uint8[33])` | `view` | `bytes20` |

---

### Key Notes & Usage Examples

**Binding to the precompile** — attach via the constant address:
```solidity
ISystem system = ISystem(SYSTEM_ADDR);
```

**`toAccountId`** — converts an H160 address to the runtime's native account ID format. Per the docs, "if no mapping exists for `addr`, the fallback account id will be returned."
```solidity
bytes memory accountId = system.toAccountId(0x1234...5678);
```

**`callerIsOrigin`** — returns `true` when the immediate caller is the top-level transaction sender, not an intermediary contract:
```solidity
require(system.callerIsOrigin(), "Must be called directly by user");
```

**`callerIsRoot`** — checks for elevated root privileges. Importantly, returning `true` implies `callerIsOrigin()` is also `true`, since only the origin can be root.

**`minimumBalance`** — returns the existential deposit (accounts below this are removed from state):
```solidity
uint minBalance = system.minimumBalance();
require(msg.value >= minBalance, "Below existential deposit");
```

**`weightLeft`** — returns remaining computational budget as two components:
```solidity
(uint64 refTime, uint64 proofSize) = system.weightLeft();
require(refTime > 1000000, "Insufficient weight remaining");
```

**`terminate`** — self-destructs the calling contract and sends its balance to a beneficiary. It reverts if called from a constructor, static context, delegate context, or a contract with balance locks.

**`sr25519Verify`** — validates signatures from Polkadot-native wallets using the sr25519 scheme:
```solidity
bool isValid = system.sr25519Verify(sig, message, pubKey);
require(isValid, "Invalid signature");
```

